a Markdown list item


302
00:14:20.494 --> 00:14:22.229 line:-2 align:center
starting with
the word Parameter


303
00:14:22.296 --> 00:14:24.498 line:-2 align:center
followed by the name
of your method's parameter,


304
00:14:24,565 --> 00:14:27,968 line:-2
a colon,
and then its documentation.


305
00:14:28,035 --> 00:14:30,637 line:-2
You can add a Returns section
in a very similar way,


306
00:14:30,704 --> 00:14:34,274 line:-2
this time by writing a Returns
delimiter followed by a colon


307
00:14:34,341 --> 00:14:37,544 line:-2
and a description of what
your method returns.


308
00:14:37,611 --> 00:14:41,281 line:-2
But what if your method
has multiple parameters?


309
00:14:41.348 --> 00:14:44.017 line:-2 align:center
In this case, the best
thing to do is to go from


310
00:14:44,084 --> 00:14:48,055 line:-2
a singular Parameter delimiter
to a plural Parameters one.


311
00:14:48,121 --> 00:14:49,690 line:-2
This works much the same
